<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id6b89d810-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e" identifier="/us/usc/t33/s925"><num value="925">§ 925.</num><heading> Witness fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Witnesses summoned in a proceeding before a deputy commissioner or whose depositions are taken shall receive the same fees and mileage as witnesses in courts of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id6b89d811-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-03-04/ch509/s25">Mar. 4, 1927, ch. 509, § 25</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1437">44 Stat. 1437</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
